name: Plains
set_name: Global Series Jiang Yanggu & Mu Yanling

name: Plains
flavor_text: Seeking to learn why the ancestors have fallen silent, you've made your way to their ancient cairns.

name: Plains
flavor_text: Searching for a vanished caravan that was bound for Silverymoon, you've come to a bank of mysterious fog.

name: Plains
flavor_text: Venturing beneath the desert sands, you've discovered an alien power pulsing with inconceivable energy.

name: Island
set_name: Global Series Jiang Yanggu & Mu Yanling

name: Island
flavor_text: In crystal-studded waters far below the surface, you've discovered an incubating egg of mysterious origin.

name: Island
flavor_text: After careful study, you've determined that the giant ruins served to track the movement of the planets ... and they will soon align once more.

name: Island
flavor_text: As your ship clears the edge of Waterdeep harbor, you notice pirate sails on the horizon. What has made them so bold?

name: Island
flavor_text: Alarmed by the news you brought, the storm giant king of the Maelstrom has called his kin to council.

name: Swamp
flavor_text: As a plague ravages the world above, you've made your way into the Underdark in search of a fungal panacea.

name: Swamp
flavor_text: Your search for a stolen artifact has brought you to the edge of the Mere of Dead Men.

name: Swamp
flavor_text: As you trudge through the sewers of Baldur's Gate it dawns on you: where are all the rats?

name: Swamp
flavor_text: You expected to meet hostile drow in this ancient ruin . . . but they fled long ago. What darkness could have driven them out?

name: Mountain
set_name: Global Series Jiang Yanggu & Mu Yanling

name: Mountain
flavor_text: You meant to simply rest in Hundelstone, but the miners have told you stories of whispers in the dark below.

name: Mountain
flavor_text: Your path lies across the Spine of the World, where every cave hides some new danger.

name: Mountain
flavor_text: You've ventured deep into the heart of the mountain to determine what can calm its quaking rage.

name: Mountain
flavor_text: As you make camp near the ancient ruin, you hear the sound of drums echoing in halls where no dwarf has lived in generations.

name: Forest
flavor_text: Before the elf queen will aid you, you must find a way to cure the strange rot afflicting the roots of the ancient trees.

name: Forest
set_name: Global Series Jiang Yanggu & Mu Yanling

name: Forest
flavor_text: As the sun reaches its zenith on the day of the solstice, a castle shimmers into view on the hilltop, just as the ancient text predicted.

name: Forest
flavor_text: As you venture deeper under the boughs of Neverwinter Wood, arrows in a tree trunk suggest you might not be welcome.

name: Forest
flavor_text: As monsters from the Underdark rampage across the world above, you've delved deep underground to determine what has driven them upward.

name: Plains
flavor_text: You've traced the tensions in Ten-Towns to the dwindling reindeer populations ... but what has been hunting them?

name: Plains
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: You've heard rumors of bandits along the Coast Way, but your journey so far has even surprisingly uneventful.

name: Plains
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: Lady Bormul claims an owlbear has been trampling her fields, but there's something unnatural about the tracks it left behind.

name: Plains
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: After spending all day trying to track down a rare tome, you're about to give up when you hear your name whispered from a dark alley.

name: Plains
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: You arrive at Baldur's Gate with instructions to head straight to the heart of the rumor mill: the bakery.

name: Island
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: As you sail past the imposing Seatower of Balduran, you realize that breaking your friend out of that prison will be much harder than you thought.

name: Island
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: As you gaze down upon Wyrm's Crossing, you hear distant cries of alarm, and you notice that all traffic on the bridge has come to a halt.

name: Island
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: You're about to disembark to find the harbormaster when you spot a merfolk darting underneath your ship.

name: Island
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: The ship's captain promised she'd get you safely to the Netherese ruin, but *she* is the one who just washed overboard.

name: Forest
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: You know that hiexel bark produces a lot of smoke when burned, but why would Rilsa Rael need so much of it?

name: Forest
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: The lights in the cavern glow and fade, glow and fade in a rhythm that must have a deeper meaning, if only you can figure it out.

name: Forest
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: You continue to mutter and complain as you trip over yet another gnarled root. From behind the nearest tree trunk, something mutters back.

name: Forest
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: You're on your way home when you spot the gates of a strange city . . . one that isn't on the map and wasn't here when you traveled this path four days ago.

name: Mountain
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: As you explore the slums of the Outer City, you keep hearing rumors of a den of werewolves in the caves below Dusthawk Hill.

name: Mountain
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: Lord Jannath sent you to secure the mine from gnoll raiders, but so far you haven't seen any gnolls . . . or, for that matter, any miners.

name: Mountain
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: Rumor holds that powerful artifacts and untold wealth are hidden away in Ramazith's Tower, and today you plan to find out for yourself.

name: Mountain
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: As you pause mid-climb to catch your breath, you'd swear you can hear a heartbeat pulsing deep within the mountain.

name: Swamp
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: Now that you've clearly hit the "marsh" part of Lizard Marsh, you begin to worry about the "lizard" part.

name: Swamp
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: The sudden sinkhole was surprising enough, but nothing could have prepared you for the ancient city that was hidden underneath.

name: Swamp
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: The old wizard's experiments destroyed the castle centuries ago. So why does some of the rubble look recent?

name: Swamp
set_name: Commander Legends: Battle for Baldur's Gate
flavor_text: At the mouth of the sewer pipe, you realize it's massive enough that even a giant could walk through without stooping. That gives you an idea . . .
